---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const updated = 'June 14, 2026';
---

<Base title="Terms of Service — lirova">
  <section class="detail wrap">
    <a href="/" class="back">&larr; Back home</a>
    <div class="prose">
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="meta-line">Last updated: {updated}</p>

      <p>
        These terms govern your use of the <strong>lirova</strong> website
        (<code>lirova.github.io</code>), any pilot engagement, and any self-hosted
        software we provide. By using them, you agree to these terms.
      </p>

      <h2>1. What we provide</h2>
      <p>
        lirova designs, builds, and operates automation and AI systems, and offers
        scoped pilot engagements. Software we provide is generally
        <strong>self-hosted</strong> &mdash; it runs in your own environment, on
        your own infrastructure, with your own credentials.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Pilots and engagements</h2>
      <p>
        The specific scope, deliverables, and any fees of a pilot or engagement are
        agreed separately in writing. A free pilot is offered as-is to evaluate
        fit, and either party may end it at any time.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Your responsibilities</h2>
      <p>
        Because the software runs in your environment, you are responsible for your
        own infrastructure, credentials, API keys, backups, and for using the
        software in compliance with applicable laws and the terms of any
        third-party services it connects to (for example, your Google account).
      </p>

      <h2>4. Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>
        Unless agreed otherwise in writing, lirova retains ownership of the
        underlying software and tooling, and grants you a license to use it for your
        own operations. Your data and your content remain entirely yours.
      </p>

      <h2>5. No warranty</h2>
      <p>
        The website, pilots, and software are provided <strong>&ldquo;as is&rdquo;
        and &ldquo;as available,&rdquo;</strong> without warranties of any kind,
        express or implied, including merchantability, fitness for a particular
        purpose, and non-infringement. Automation and AI systems can make mistakes;
        you are responsible for reviewing outcomes before relying on them.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by law, lirova will not be liable for any
        indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages, or for any loss of
        data, profits, or business, arising from your use of the website, a pilot,
        or the software.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>
        Don&rsquo;t use the website or software to break the law, infringe others&rsquo;
        rights, or disrupt the service. We may decline or end an engagement at our
        discretion.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Governing law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are governed by the laws of the State of California, United
        States, without regard to its conflict-of-laws rules.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these terms as the services evolve; the &ldquo;last
        updated&rdquo; date above reflects the current version.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions? Email
        <span class="cta-email" data-b="bGlyb3ZhQHByb3Rvbi5tZQ=="></span>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script>
    document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('.cta-email').forEach((el) => {
      const addr = atob(el.dataset.b || '');
      const a = document.createElement('a');
      a.href = `mailto:${addr}`;
      a.textContent = addr;
      el.replaceWith(a);
    });
  </script>
</Base>
